Customer is requesting the ability to change group membership for designated users who are not part of the global administration group.

h4. Actual behavior:

When you import a project from Instance A into Instance B, if there's an Application Link cross linking issues, the Remote Links are not carried over.

h4. Steps to reproduce:

Instance A has ATP-1 issue linking AWD-1 issue that belongs to Instance B. When importing the ATP project into Instance B, the link should be kept and updated to reflect to the correct place.

h4. Expected behavior:

Have the remote links imported into the instance.

h4. Workaround:

*The API referenced is here:*

This step will performed after the project has been imported in the target source:

[https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.6.1/#api/2/issue-getRemoteIssueLinks]

*Basically we'd do a simple get from the source for all the issues in a project:*
{code:java}
GET URLOFSOURCE/rest/api/2/issue/{issueIdOrKey}/remotelink
{code}
{code:java}
    {
        "id": 10001,
        "self": "http://10.125.88.109:8080/jira730/rest/api/2/issue/KRIS-11/remotelink/10001",
        "application": {},
        "object": {
            "url": "https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.6.1/#api/2/issue-getRemoteIssueLinks",
            "title": "test",
            "icon": {
                "url16x16": "https://docs.atlassian.com/favicon.ico"
            },
            "status": {
                "icon": {}
            }
        }
    }

{code}
*All you need to do is change the URL to the target instance and the call to a post, the JSON doesn't need to be reformated*
{code:java}
POST /rest/api/2/issue/{issueIdOrKey}/remotelink
{code}
{code:java}
    {
        "id": 10001,
        "self": "http://10.125.88.109:8080/jira730/rest/api/2/issue/KRIS-11/remotelink/10001",
        "application": {},
        "object": {
            "url": "https://docs.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/api/REST/7.6.1/#api/2/issue-getRemoteIssueLinks",
            "title": "test",
            "icon": {
                "url16x16": "https://docs.atlassian.com/favicon.ico"
            },
            "status": {
                "icon": {}
            }
        }
    }

{code}

h3. Summary 
 The following command can be used to reproduce this problem:
{code:java}
 curl -D- -u user:password -X PUT --data "{\"fields\":{\"timetracking\":{\"remainingEstimate\":\"3d 1h\"}}}" -H "Content-Type: application/json" http://url/rest/api/latest/issue/issuekey
{code}

Result:
{code:java}
      "timetracking":{  
         "originalEstimate":"3d 1h",
         "remainingEstimate":"3d 1h",
        ....
      },
{code}

Setting *originalEstimate* updates *remainingEstimate* also, so attempted workaround by resetting originalEstimate to whatever it was before the change does not work.

h3. Steps to reproduce:
 # create an issue
 # set the original estimate (eg: 2h)
 # log work in the issue (eg: 10 mins) . Refer to screenshot BeforeRESTCommand.png
 # run REST command to update the Remaining Estimate
 # refresh issue view screen and the Original Estimate is also updated . Refer to screenshot AfterRESTCommand.png


h3. Workaround

Two possible workarounds:
# The issue does not occur if you enable [time tracking 'Legacy Mode'|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver075/configuring-time-tracking-935391805.html#Configuringtimetracking-legacymodeAbout'LegacyMode']
# Always set both,  *originalEstimate* and *remainingEstimate*. This way it works fine:
#- REQUEST: {code:borderStyle=solid}
{
"fields": {
	"timetracking": { 
		"remainingEstimate": "55m",
		"originalEstimate":"2h"
		}
	}
} 
{code}
#- RESULT: {code:borderStyle=solid}
      "timetracking":{  
         "originalEstimate":"2h",
         "remainingEstimate":"55m",
         "originalEstimateSeconds":7200,
         "remainingEstimateSeconds":3300
      }, 
{code}

